    "This stage represents the incubation period when an individual has been in contact with the disease but is not yet showing symptoms or capable of transmitting it to others.",
    "This group comprises individuals who are infected with the disease and capable of transmitting it to others.",
    "Recovered (R): These individuals have recovered from the disease and are no longer susceptible to it.",
    "In some cases, they may also be immune to reinfection.",
    "\"Metapopulation\" in this context refers to the fact that the model considers not just a single, homogeneous population but multiple populations in different geographical locations, such as major cities in China."
